                           <locus target="#120vb">Fol. 120vb</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 120vb: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘደጃዝማች፡ ካሣ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለቤት፡ ማርያም፡ ለማርያም፡ ብርሃነ፡ ዖዳ፡ ወስመ፡ ጥምቀቱ፡ ወልደ፡ አረጋዊ፡ ወስመ፡ አቡሁ፡ ኪዳነ፡ ማርያም፡ ወስሙ፡ እሙ፡ ወለተ፡ ዮሓንስ፡ ታድኅኖ፡ እምክራ፡ ሥጋ፡ ወነፍስ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፤</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in the main hand. Däğğazmač Kaśa (later šum ʿagame) donated the manuscript to Bet Maryam. His baptismal name, Wäldä ʾArägawi, the baptismal names of his father is Kidanä Maryam (ras Sǝbḥat ʾArägawi) and his mother, Wälättä Yoḥannǝs, are also mentioned.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Note erased: fol. 120vb.&#xD;
- The names of Gäbreʾel and Mikaʾel are written in alternating red and black letters: fol. 17vb.&#xD;
- Omitted words or lines are written interlineally: fols. 22ra, 37rb, 37va, 43ra.</item>
                     </list>
